<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 3:27PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Giles,
southwestern Craig and northwestern Montgomery Counties through 400
PM EDT...
At 327 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Mountain Lake, moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Blacksburg...
Pembroke...
Newport...
Mountain Lake...
Prices Fork...
Eggleston...
and Cascades.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
